.\" DO NOT MODIFY THIS FILE!
.TH man 1 "11 Nov 2020" "@sentinel_VERSION@" "sentinel manual"
.SH NAME
sentinel \- the mutation testing tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
sentinel [SOURCE_ROOT_PATH] {OPTIONS}
.SH DESCRIPTION
sentinel is the mutation testing tool for C/C++ projects.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS sentinel [SOURCE_ROOT_PATH] {OPTIONS}
Run mutation test in standalone mode
.TP
SOURCE_ROOT_PATH
source root directory.
.TP
-v, --verbose
Verbosity
.TP
-w[PATH], --workspace=[PATH]
Sentinel workspace directory for all run artifacts. Default: ./sentinel_workspace
.TP
-o[PATH], --output-dir=[PATH]
Directory for saving output. If output-dir is not given, pass generating output file.
.TP
-b[PATH], --build-dir=[PATH]
Directory where compile_commands.json file exists. Default: .
.TP
--test-result-dir=[PATH]
Test command output directory
.TP
--build-command=[SH_CMD]
Shell command to build source
.TP
--test-command=[SH_CMD]
Shell command to execute test
.TP
--generator=[gen]
Select mutant generator type, one of ['uniform', 'random', 'weighted']. Default: uniform
.TP
--test-result-extention=[EXTENSION...]
Test command output file extensions.
.TP
-t[EXTENSION...], --extension=[EXTENSION...]
Extentions of source file which could be mutated.
.TP
-e[PATH...], --exclude=[PATH...]
exclude file or path
.TP
--coverage=[COV.INFO...]
lcov-format coverage result file
.TP
-s[SCOPE], --scope=[SCOPE]
Diff scope, one of ['commit', 'all']. Default: all
.TP
-l[COUNT], --limit=[COUNT]
Maximum generated mutable count. Default: 10
.TP
--timeout=[TIME_SEC]
Time limit (sec) for test-command. If 0, there is no time limit. If auto, time limit is automatically set using test execution time of the original code. Default: auto
.TP
--kill-after=[TIME_SEC]
Send SIGKILL if test-command is still running after timeout. If 0, SIGKILL is not sent. This option has no meaning when timeout is set 0. Default: 60
.TP
--seed=[SEED]
Select random seed. Default: random
.TP
--init
Generate a sentinel.yaml configuration template in the current directory and exit.
If sentinel.yaml already exists, prompts for confirmation before overwriting.
.TP
--config=[PATH]
Path to a YAML configuration file. If not specified, sentinel.yaml in the current directory is used automatically when present.
.TP
--no-statusline
Disable the terminal status line even when stdout is a TTY.
By default, a live status line is shown at the bottom of the terminal displaying the current phase, mutant progress, result counters, mutation score, and elapsed time.
The status line is automatically suppressed when output is piped or redirected.
.SH CONFIGURATION FILE
Sentinel supports a YAML configuration file (\fBsentinel.yaml\fR) as an alternative to passing all options on the command line.
When \fBsentinel\fR is invoked, it automatically looks for \fBsentinel.yaml\fR in the current working directory.
Use \fB--config\fR to specify a different file.
.PP
CLI arguments always take priority over values in the configuration file.
.PP
Supported keys (all optional):
.TP
\fBsource-root\fR
Source root directory.
.TP
\fBverbose\fR
Enable verbose logging (boolean).
.TP
\fBdebug\fR
Enable debug logging (boolean).
.TP
\fBworkspace\fR
Workspace directory for all run artifacts.
.TP
\fBoutput-dir\fR
Directory for output reports.
.TP
\fBcwd\fR
Change to this directory before running.
.TP
\fBbuild-dir\fR
Build command output directory.
.TP
\fBcompiledb\fR
Explicit path to directory containing compile_commands.json.
.TP
\fBscope\fR
Diff scope: \fBcommit\fR or \fBall\fR.
.TP
\fBextension\fR
List of source file extensions to mutate.
.TP
\fBpattern\fR
List of paths or glob patterns to constrain the diff.
.TP
\fBexclude\fR
List of fnmatch-style patterns to exclude from mutation.
.TP
\fBlimit\fR
Maximum number of mutants to generate.
.TP
\fBbuild-command\fR
Shell command to build the source.
.TP
\fBtest-command\fR
Shell command to execute tests.
.TP
\fBtest-result-dir\fR
Directory containing test command output.
.TP
\fBtest-result-extension\fR
List of file extensions of test output files.
.TP
\fBcoverage\fR
List of lcov-format coverage result files.
.TP
\fBgenerator\fR
Mutant generator type: \fBuniform\fR, \fBrandom\fR, or \fBweighted\fR.
.TP
\fBtimeout\fR
Time limit (seconds) for the test command. \fB0\fR = no limit, \fBauto\fR = auto-detect.
.TP
\fBkill-after\fR
Seconds after timeout before SIGKILL is sent. \fB0\fR = disabled.
.TP
\fBseed\fR
Random seed for mutant selection.
.TP
\fBoperator\fR
List of mutation operators to use (AOR, BOR, LCR, ROR, SDL, SOR, UOI). Omit to use all.
.TP
\fBno-statusline\fR
Disable the terminal status line even when stdout is a TTY (boolean).
.SH REPORTING BUGS
sentinel issue tracker: <https://github.com/shift-left-test/sentinel/issues>
.SH SEE ALSO
sentinel repository: <https://github.com/shift-left-test/sentinel>, Mutation Testing on Wikipedia: <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mutation_testing>
